The student works on his/her Master's thesis independently under the supervision of a university teacher / teachers or a practitioner and a university teacher. Research problems are negotiated with the supervisor and discussed in Masters' seminars. Master's thesis is compiled according to the requirements of the Institute of Education. In case of a large scale project / research task which is implemented as an integral whole, a team-based implementation is possible, given that the role and input of each team member can be established.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is: - to facilitate the students to deepen their knowledge and skills on planning and implementing a research/development project on learning and teaching or management of an educational institution; - to facilitate the acquisition of skills concerning the implementation of theoretical knowledge and empirical experience in practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: 1. Establishes a problem statement based on scientific literature, formulates the aim of the research and the research questions and/or hypotheses in accordance with the problem statement. 2. Finds, analyzes and synthesizes relevant scientific literature, the theoretical approaches and research results presented in it. 3. Chooses the most suitable research method for the study, justifies the choice, processes and analyzes research data. 4. Presents the results of the research and interprets them based on the theoretical framework and the results of previous research. 5. Follows the academic writing requirements in accordance with the theses formatting guide. 6. Presents the results of the work and defends them in public academic discussion.
